---
// A static comparison, not a unified system diagram. Reachy Mini CLI and
// ARM101 CLI stay in separate bounded panels so no connector can imply a
// shared runtime. The Reachy panel also splits external agent attach, folded
// forge cognition, and the stash API into separate tracks. ARM map production
// ends at the persisted artifact; the possible flex gate is drawn with a stop
// bar and an explicit FUTURE / NOT CONNECTED label.
//
// The SVG has its own accessible name and complete description. A visible
// prose transcription follows it for readers who prefer text or encounter a
// user agent with incomplete SVG accessibility support. There is no motion,
// JavaScript, external asset, or client request: reduced-motion users receive
// the same fully composed diagram.
---

<figure class="mind-body-diagram">
  <div class="diagram-viewport">
    <svg
      viewBox="0 0 1080 780"
      fill="none"
      role="img"
      aria-labelledby="mind-body-diagram-title mind-body-diagram-desc"
    >
      <title id="mind-body-diagram-title">
        The agent as mind, code as symbolic nervous system, and robot as physical body
      </title>
      <desc id="mind-body-diagram-desc">
        Architecture comparison of two separate products and runtimes. In Reachy Mini CLI,
        the shipped external agent attach sends runtime events from the symbolic nervous
        system to an agent mind made of a harness plus model. The separate cognition output
        returns as a durable intent, then passes through validation, arbitration, the
        robot-specific symbolic runtime, and only then reaches the physical body. A separate
        shipped folded live cognition track sends generated code through forge validation
        before an auto-activated reaction is retained; forge is not a tool on external agent
        attach. A separate Python API only track can retain a stash behavior record; stash is
        not an external-attach tool. In ARM101 CLI, servo load and stall feedback from the
        physical arm enters the symbolic runtime, and the shipped arm explore track writes an
        append-only log and a persisted reachability map. A dashed line stops before arm flex:
        arm flex does not consume this map, and that connector is future and not connected.
        No line joins the two products or claims a shared runtime, shipped integration, or one
        autonomous closed learning loop.
      </desc>

